The paper deals with the concept of vector linear solutions in networks, which involves information theory and network information theory (cs.IT), as well as network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the properties of networks and their solvability, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper presents mathematical proofs and analysis, which is related to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper could also be categorized under the sub-field of signal processing (cs.SI) due to its focus on the transmission and processing of information in networks.
